text:
DOMImplementationImpl throws two different exceptions when passing a null or 
empty string to createDocumentType() respectively.

If passing a null as the qualifiedName, publicId, or systemId, xerces throws:

org.w3c.dom.DOMException: DOM002 Illegal character
        at org.apache.xerces.dom.DOMImplementationImpl.createDocumentType
           (DOMImplementationImpl.java:155)

If passing an empty string as the qualifiedName, publicId, or systemId, xerces 
throws:

java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
        at org.apache.xerces.dom.DocumentImpl.isXMLName(DocumentImpl.java:1519)
        at org.apache.xerces.dom.DOMImplementationImpl.createDocumentType
           (DOMImplementationImpl.java:154)

DocumentTypeImpl is able to handle these two cases with no problem.

The following code snippet will cause the exception:
// <snip/>
DOMImplementationImpl dom = new DOMImplementationImpl ();
DocumentType doctype1 = dom.createDocumentType (null, null, "uri://foo");

// DOMException: DOM002 Illegal character
// <snip/>

DocumentType doctype2 = dom.createDocumentType ("", "", "uri://foo");

// ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
//<snip/>
